1 OK Clara Bow silent film from 1927 , it 's a spin - off of Rain , with Bow playing the half - Hawaiian wild daughter of the local pineapple king who falls in love with the staid English engineer -- Clive Brook . Bow competes with the local widow ( Arlette Marchal ) for his attentions , but both women get a big surprise when his wife shows up ( Patricia Dupont ) . The predatory wife is ready for a divorce until she discovers he might be on the verge of a fortune . Bow settles her hash fast.<br /><br />Bow has personality to spare and has a few great scenes : her opening nude bath , her hula in a grass skirt , and the dog rescue scene with Bow and Brook doing their own stunts.<br /><br />Note : the IMDb credit list is wrong . The film credits ( from the DVD I have ) list Patricia Dupont as playing Mrs. Haldane --- not Margaret Truax as listed on IMDb .
